{"questionId":"9070360","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>One suggestion for the reduction of carbon footprints is the use of biofuels, such as&nbsp;vegetable oils, as a substitute for petroleum based fuels.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>State the formula of a fuel that might be produced from the vegetable oil whose formula&nbsp;is shown.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4499/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-08_om_09.42.54.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/HP3/ENG/TZ1/13,b\"></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>R–CO–O–CH<sub>3</sub> / RCOOMe</p>\n<p><strong><em>OR</em></strong></p>\n<p>R–CO–O–C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>5</sub> / RCOOEt</p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9070360","referenceCode":"18M.3.hl.TZ1.13b","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the formula of a fuel that might be produced from the vegetable oil whose formula is shown.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Options","Options","C: Energy","C.4 Solar energy","Options","C: Energy"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}